Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_2547
Response Text: There's a lot of new arts grants that pop up once, usually for a one-time timely issue like covering a bridge that's being renovated with a mural or creating a public art piece around a theme that's popular, one time. I would like to see more consistent funding and other types of grants that allow organizations to pay rent at facilities and pay their staff living wage. Pay time and put some funding toward outreach- to get new people aware of the grants, non English speakers and folks who live outside the city limits. Create a cool app or at least a modern, mobile friendly, easy to use multilingual database where artists can register to be a "registered vendor", see opportunities like grants or space rental, and add those things to their profile so they can apply for permits and have everything in one easy to use profile. Other apps function like this outside the city- you can manager data and payments for other things so why not your grants, permits, active applications, etc? The more you invest in easy to use systems the more people can help themselves and each other with these processes. More transparency in general. If the City can't offer a service, more straightforward direction about what they do and can't do. More transparency about the alcohol policies for events. Review the policy on insurance for renters- these policies are prohibitive.

